Mission Report ___________________________________________________________________
Greetings Detective,
You stumble across a crime scene and are required to find two pieces of evidence to sample.
You are given an evidence grid, but it is up to you to decide the number of rows and columns on the grid.
After entering the dimensions for the grid, you must input row and column guesses until you find both samples.
If your guess is wrong left (<), right (>), up (^), or down (v) arrows are displayed in the place of your guess accordingly.
Good luck Detective. The world is counting on you.
____________________________________________________________________
